[3] Cholera - Somalia
Date: Sun 7 Jan 2018
Source: WHO, Government of Somalia [edited]
https://reliefweb.int/report/somalia/situation-report-acute-watery-diarrheacholera-epidemiological-week-1-1-7-january-2018


Situation Report for Acute Watery Diarrhea/Cholera, Epidemiological Week 1 (1 - 7 Jan 2018)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Highlights
- A total of 90 new cases including one death of AWD [acute watery diarrhea] were reported in week one compared to 53 cases in week 52 in 2 Region.
- In Hiraan, new AWD/Cholera cases were reported in Beletweyne while in Banadir new AWD/Cholera cases were reported in Daynile district.
- A cumulative total of 90 cases and one death have been reported in 8 districts of 2 regions of South central since January 2018.
- The new AWD/cholera cases reported in Beletweyne and Daynile districts are a continuation of AWD/Cholera cases that affected 9 districts of 2 states of Somalia.
- Out of 7 stool samples collected from Banadir region 2 were positive for _V. cholerae_, Ogawa, O1.

Key Figures
- 90 new cases
- 1 death
- 47 percent of the new cases were female
- 58 percent of the cases were below 5 years
- 84 percent of the cases did not receive Oral cholera vaccine
- 9 district reported new AWD cases in 2 region
- 90 cumulative cases for 2018
- 1 cumulative death
- 1.1 percent overall case fatality rate

