[4] Cholera - Congo DR (Kinshasa)
Date: Thu 18 Jan 2018 16h21
Source: Journal Du Cameroun [edited]
https://www.journalducameroun.com/en/drc-suspected-cholera-kills-32-out-of-725-reported-cases/


The capital city of Kinshasa has registered 725 suspected cases of cholera including 32 deaths, the coordinator of the National Cholera Programme in the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC) has announced. According to Dr. Jos√© Bompange, 26 health zones out of the 35 in Kinshasa are affected by "suspected" cholera, so called because currently they only have biological confirmation from 3 health zones that today constitute the epicenter of the epidemic.

According to him, the density of the city which now has nearly 13 million inhabitants and the conditions in some neighborhoods with sometimes insufficient water supply, explain the resurgence of the epidemic in Kinshasa. The overflow of rainwater also acts as an amplifying factor, he added.

On [Tue 9 Jan 2018], DR Congo's Health Minister estimated that the cholera epidemic could worsen in the coming days in Kinshasa, following recurring floods recently in the city. Meanwhile, WHO handed over to the Congolese government on [Mon 8 Jan 2018] 11 tons of drugs to support the authorities' response against cholera. WHO Regional Director for Africa Ms. Rebecca Matshidiso Moeti, on a working visit to DR Congo, presented the medicines to a representative of the Health minister.

--
